Controversial ANC politician Mduduzi Manana has allegedly taken a decision to step down as an MP. This after the National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) decided on Wednesday to not prosecute him for the alleged assault of his then domestic worker Christine Wiro. NPA south Gauteng spokeswoman Phindile Mjonondwane confirmed that Manana was now a free man. TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE